LEARN HOME SCREEN:
The Learn section represents the foundation of everything you need to know to really get the most out of QOT. There are 55 strategies categorized by four main pillars, Movement, Nutrition, Mindset, and Recovery, as well as foundational videos and habituation strategies.To get into a category, simply tap on the bubble. The more complete your circles are, the more strategies of that type you have reviewed. The more complete your circles are, the more strategies of that type you have reviewed. Once your circle is complete, you’ve reviewed all of that category.
STRATEGY SCREEN:
Any strategies you have read will appear translucent. Each strategy bubble shows the title of the strategy and an estimated time that it will take you to read the strategy. Tapping on the bubble will take you to the full text of the strategy, which will explain what the strategy is and how you can use it. If you don’t have time to read the entire text, you can swipe to the left to access bullet point or audio forms of the strategy. You can scroll between the different strategies by swiping right and left. At the top of the screen, you will see which category of strategy you are in
WHILE IN TEXT SECTION OF A STRATEGY:
Swipe left to view the bullet points of this strategy, which make up a short, easy-to-read summary that explains it in more detail. Swipe left twice to access the audio file of the strategy. Each of the QOT55 strategies has an audio component. You can listen to this in your car, during your commute, or while in the office. To exit the strategy, tap on the arrow in the top left.
WHAT’S HOT HELP ICON:
What’s Hot helps you get more insights into how the QOT55 Strategies are applied. This section will contain articles of current events, client experiences, and unique insights on new studies that are happening and how you can analyze these events from a QOT perspective. The most recent 10 What’s Hot posts will be displayed in this section. They each have a title, how long each item takes to read, and the date the article was posted. What’s Hot also includes Tignum’s biweekly blogs. One of the benefits of being a QOT user is that you get first access to our newest content. To read an article, simply tap on its picture or title.
